{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nGates must each read their own kind, and reopen must invalidate WITHOUT mutating records.\nThis slice flips the gates from the legacy single `signature` mirror to the kind-keyed\n`attestations` map + validity-on-read, and removes the now-obsolete reopen mutation.\n## What\nAdd `compute_validity(attestation, ticket_state, kind, *, repo_root=None) -> {\"valid\": bool,\n\"reason\": str}` in the verification layer. It ASSUMES the attestation is already\nHMAC-certified (the caller runs verify first) and adds ONLY the per-kind lifecycle/freshness\nlayer; it REUSES the existing plan-review material fingerprint\n(`orchestrator.material_fingerprint`) as the single source of the material field set (no new\nconstant). Migrate the gates to read `attestations[kind]` via verify + compute_validity:\n`claim_gate_check` -> `plan-review`; the close gate + completion child-closure check\n(`completion.py`, currently `verify_signature(cid).get(\"verdict\")`) -> `completion-verifier`.\nPAIRED removal (no gap): REMOVE `retire_attested_pin` (signing.py) and its reopen call\n(transition.py) IN THIS SAME slice, because compute_validity's reopen-awareness\n(`signed_at >= last_reopened_at`, data recorded by 114f) now replaces it — they land\ntogether so reopen-invalidation is never missing.\n## Scope\n`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/attest.py` (`claim_gate_check`, `compute_validity`),\n`src/rebar/_commands/transition.py` (close gate; remove retire_attested_pin reopen call),\n`src/rebar/signing.py` (remove retire_attested_pin), `src/rebar/llm/completion.py`.\n## Depends on\nRequires 114f (attestations map, last_reopened_at) and cc1b (verify_signature kind=) merged.\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `compute_validity(attestation, ticket_state, kind, *, repo_root=None)` returns `{\"valid\": bool, \"reason\": str}`, assumes certified, reuses the existing material fingerprint (no new constant).\n- [ ] Claim gate verifies+validates `plan-review`; close + child-closure verify+validate `completion-verifier`, reading `attestations[kind]`.\n- [ ] completion valid = certified AND closed AND not-reopened-since AND material-unchanged-since `signed_at`.\n- [ ] plan-review valid = existing freshness (material + filesystem code-drift) AND not-reopened-since.\n- [ ] `retire_attested_pin` + its reopen call removed IN THIS SLICE, paired with compute_validity (no window with missing reopen-invalidation); no transition mutates any attestation record.\n\n## Added (review)\n- ADR: add `docs/adr/` entry 'Reopen invalidation: validity-on-read over mutation' (and a\n  short CLAUDE.md/plan-review-gate note) recording the old write-time approach\n  (retire_attested_pin), the gap it had, and the invariant that gates MUST call\n  compute_validity rather than mutate attestation records.\n- CHILD-CLOSURE call site: `_child_closure_findings` (completion.py:94) migrates from\n  `rebar.verify_signature(cid).get(\"verdict\") != \"certified\"` to verifying the\n  completion-verifier kind AND running compute_validity, i.e.\n  `compute_validity(signing.verify_signature(cid, kind=\"completion-verifier\"), child_state, \"completion-verifier\")`.\n  This requires the public `rebar.verify_signature` facade (rebar/__init__.py) to accept +\n  pass through `kind=` (plumbed by cc1b); 929e plumbs the facade if cc1b has not.\n## Acceptance Criteria (added)\n- [ ] An ADR (docs/adr/) + a CLAUDE.md/plan-review-gate note records the validity-on-read consistency model and the 'gates call compute_validity, never mutate records' invariant.\n- [ ] `_child_closure_findings` verifies kind='completion-verifier' (not the plan-review default) and runs compute_validity; the `rebar.verify_signature` facade accepts/passes `kind=`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782796018137910001,"uuid":"302422ca-5ec9-4544-b996-133d1b991473"}